Found the plane of Steve Fossett, a millionaire who disappeared a year ago
The remains of Steve Fossett's plane have been found, a millionaire who disappeared on September 3, 2007, while flying over the Nevada desert.
The remains were found on a plateau at an altitude of 10,000 feet in the Mammoth Lakes region of Sierra Nevada, on the border between California and Nevada.
However, there were no human remains inside the plane.
Madera County Sheriff John Anderson, has resolved the remaining doubts: "The plane has been found, we have sent a team, and we now have the certainty that it is the exact same plane that Steve Fossett was flying on the day he disappeared", he told a press conference.
The Sheriff's Office has confirmed that no human remains were found on the plane or in the surrounding area.
The 63-year-old millionaire has been presumed dead since February.
The US Transportation Safety Board (NTSB) announced that a few hours after the wreckage was identified, an investigation team was dispatched and eventually identified the aircraft: it was a Bellanca 8kcab, missing since September 3, 2007, when Fossett took off from Yerington, Nevada, on a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, still in California, not far from the Nevada border, some of Fossett's personal effects were found by a couple near their residence in Mammoth Lakes.
These are two documents with Fossett's name on them, both issued by the Illinois Federal Aviation Administration, cash and a jacket.
The search for Fossett was suspended a month after his disappearance.
